metadata.name: seq00 #36
metadata.description:
seq00 is a graphic/sound sequencer. It is composed by: high frequency sounds , low frequency sounds and noises (three types). High and low freq sounds are represented by circles and noises by lines. Each sound can have applied a sound effect (delay or reverb). 

Features based on fxrand() function:
-frequency.
-sizes.
-effects.
-color mode (white/black).
-type of sound.
-number of sounds.
...

Click mouse-> Start/stop the sequence.
press any key -> loop mode

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Limina #180
metadata.description:
Limina is a study of the fine line between order and chaos.

Each piece of the collection is made up of just one or two lines. These lines are defined by thousands of points that are chosen, one by one, by a simple algorithm moving across the canvas. What arises from that simple concept is a surprising variety of intricate patterns, accidental symmetries and traces of order in chaotic structures. 

Limina is a meditation on the concept of emergence, a concept that lies at the heart of generative art. The algorithm that defines the core of the series is only capable of making one simple choice: left, right, up or down? As it moves across the canvas, it leaves a trace of points that are connected by a curve. The order in which these points are chosen and the tightness of the curve connecting them is what creates the visual diversity of Limina. As these values fluctuate, symmetries emerge and break down again, forms, patterns and ornaments are created and combined to form both complex structures and simple abstractions. 

Limina shows the potential of minimalist generative concepts to generate visually dense and unexpected results. 

Press 's' to save your image.

metadata.name: Knockout #87
metadata.description:
An exploration of screen printing techniques and how these effects can be achieved in generative work. The halftone effect works by placing very small dots next to each other to give the illusion of new shades and hues. Each Knockout samples three colors for the main composition and runs small sections of the canvas back through the machine after shuffling the base palette. The secondary passes vary in size, creating interesting emergent patterns on the overlap.

Press 's' in live view to save a .png

Built and tested with Chrome on Apple silicon. Some outputs may take up to 20s on slower machines.

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: Bound #278
metadata.description:
Knots bind and hold, mark time, and unite. But the power of a well-tied knot isn't only to fasten ‚Äì it also symbolizes how tightly one holds their pledges. Whether a commitment to a partner, community, or oneself ‚Äì the longevity of a deeply held bond is often marked with a symbol of passing time, like knots tied in a rope.

Let these ropes remind us of the binds we hold ‚Äì new ones, lengthy ones, unbreakable ones, and even those we‚Äôve had to untie. In plain view, these knots invite us to contemplate what our bonds mean to us, and to see them anew.

metadata.name: Organicon, variation I #508
metadata.description:
Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
A unique generator creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation I is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. Warning: the preview thumbnail is a pale shadow of live view.

Interface: a first mouse click clears the screen, creates an new iteration and enables active mode. In active mode each iteration remains on screen for a limited amount of time before being replaced by the next. A second mouse click disables active mode. In active mode a small dot is displayed in the lower right corner. '+' and '-' zoom in and out.
